                            <comment id="15199509" author="githubbot" created="Thu, 17 Mar 2016 13:22:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;GitHub user ijuma opened a pull request:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/1088&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/1088&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-3414&quot; title=&quot;Return of MetadataCache.getAliveBrokers should not be mutated by cache updates&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-3414&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-3414&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; Return of MetadataCache.getAliveBrokers should not be mutated by cache updates&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    `Map.values` returns `DefaultValuesIterable` where the default implementation of `toSeq` is (sadly) `toStream`. `Stream` is a lazy collection and it can reflect changes to the underlying map before it&apos;s `forced`.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    I verified that the test failed before my change.&lt;/p&gt;

